'''Turael''' is the lowest level [[Slayer Master]], along with his daughter [[Spria]]. Turael resides in [[Burthorpe]]; the fastest way to reach him is to [[Teleportation|teleport]] to [[Burthorpe Games Room]] using a [[games necklace]] and running east to Turael's house, just south of the general store.

There are no level requirements to receive [[Slayer task]]s from him, and completing a task assigned by him will always reward 0 points. Blocking a task with Turael costs 40 [[Slayer reward point]]s and the block list is shared with [[Aya]] and [[Spria]].

Because the tasks he assigns are relatively easy, players often use Turael to boost their [[Slayer reward points]]. This is accomplished by completing every 50th task with a Slayer master that gives a lot of points per task, such as [[Konar quo Maten]], and using Turael for the rest of the tasks to get to every interval of 50 more quickly. You can do this every 10 tasks instead but this is not recommended due to the amount of unfavourable tasks that can be given, unless you use a  [[Slayer Master]] other than Konar.

After the events of [[While Guthix Sleeps]], he is replaced with his sister [[Aya]].

==Task changing==
Turael is capable of changing your Slayer task from another master into a less difficult one. If another master has assigned you a task Turael could assign himself, your request will not work. Additionally, Turael will refuse to change his own tasks. Tasks may be blocked at Turael to remove them from his list of assignments, allowing them to be changed if assigned by other Slayer masters.

This ability to change Slayer tasks is used in a method called "Turael skipping", which is commonly used when seeking a specific Slayer task from another master, such as a [[hydra]] task from [[Konar quo Maten]] or a [[TzHaar]] task in order to speedrun the [[Inferno]]. Players get a task from another Slayer master; if it isn't the task they want, they change their task with Turael, complete Turael's task, and repeat the process until they get the desired task.

It is possible to use this method with [[Krystilia]] as well, without resetting your active Wilderness Slayer task streak.

'''{{Colour|red|Warning}}: After a task change is processed, your [[Slayer reward point|task streak]] will also be reset to zero!'''

Note: Turael is a valid contact for the [[NPC Contact]] spell, and you can obtain tasks from them.  It is part of the [[Lunar spellbook]]. 

